assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Enea AB (publ) provides software products for telecommunication and cybersecurity industries worldwide. It offers Stratum, a resilient and distributed network data layer; Enea Aptilo Service Management Platform, a system for managing large-scale Wi-Fi services; and IoT connectivity and security solution comprising cellular IoT programmable connectivity, zero-touch Wi-Fi IoT, and IoT connectivity management platform, as well as network cyber security solutions. The company also provides Enea Access Manager, a cloud-native AAA server providing access control; Enea Policy Manager that provides the PCRF and PCF functions in 4G and 5G networks; Enea ENUM, a turnkey solution that provides a bridge between the mobile network and the internet; and Subscription Manager, a cloud-native solution, as well as unified data manager. In addition, it offers TCP Accelerator, a clientless solution that accelerates the mobile Internet experience; Encrypted Video Manager that identifies OTT video traffic and optimises it for the screen; Virtual Load Balancer, a virtualized software-based load balancer; and 5G Service Engine, a cloud-native packet flow inspection engine, as well as RAN Congestion Manager, Session Congestion Manager, Traffic Classifier, TLS Manager, and Integra Cloud-Ready Platform. Further, it provides Enea OSE, a real-time operating system for multi-processor systems; Enea Linux, a Linux distribution that accelerates time-to-market and reduces risks; and Enea OSEck, an operating system for high-performance and memory constrained applications. Additionally, it offers Enea Netbricks, a collection of highly portable networking protocols; Enea Polyhedra, a SQL database; Qosmos ixEngine, a deep packet inspection software; Qosmos Probe, a network sensor for granular visibility into network activity; Aptilo SMP Venue Wi-Fi Manager; and Zero-touch Wi-Fi IoT and Cellular IoT Connectivity services. The company was founded in 1968 and is headquartered in Kista, Sweden.
